# How to create an extension

1. Build sitepackage by using Sitepackage Builder ()
2. Create a directory in the root level named as  "packages"
3. Move your extension into packages directory
4. Define the version of your package: 
        (packages/sitepackage/composer.json > below "keywords" ) -> "version": "1.0.0",
5. Add repositories into root/composer.json
        "repositories": [ { "type": "path", "url": "packages/*" }],
6. Add your package using composer as in packages/sitepackage/composer.json > "name"
        [Terminal] ddev composer require sitepackage
7. Include sitepackage in TYPO3 Backend > TypoScript > Edit TypoScript Record > Edit the whole TS > Advanced Options
